theorem Topology.P3_of_P3_closureInterior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 (closure (interior A)) → Topology.P3 A := by
  intro hP3
  dsimp [Topology.P3] at hP3 ⊢
  intro x hxA
  -- `x` lies in `closure (interior A)` because `interior A ⊆ A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
  have hxClInt : x ∈ closure (interior A) := subset_closure hxA
  -- Apply the `P3` hypothesis for `closure (interior A)`.
  have hxInt₁ : x ∈ interior (closure (closure (interior A))) := hP3 hxClInt
  -- Simplify the double closure.
  have hxInt₂ : x ∈ interior (closure (interior A)) := by
    simpa [closure_closure] using hxInt₁
  -- Use the monotonicity lemma to pass from `closure (interior A)` to `closure A`.
  have hIncl :
      interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
    interiorClosureInterior_subset_interiorClosure (A := A)
  exact hIncl hxInt₂

theorem Topology.interior_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (A : Set X)) := by
  intro x hx
  exact subset_closure hx
